=Temples and Monasteries=
List of Temples in China

----

==Buddhist Temples==
===Imperially sponsored Cave Temple Complexes===
* Yungang [[雲岡石窟]] near Datong 大同
* Longmen [[龍門石窟]] near Luoyang 洛陽
* Tianlongshan [[天龍山]] Taiyuan 太原
* Maijishan [[麥積山石窟]] near Tianshui 天水
* Binglingsi [[炳靈寺]] near Yongjing 永靖, Gansu
* Mogaoku [[莫高窟]] near Dunhuang 敦煌, Gansu

===List of Cave Temple Complexes sorted by Provinces===
GANSU 
* Wenshushan 文殊山石窟
* Tiantishan 天梯山石窟 (Heavenly Ladder Mountain) on 祁連山
* Binglinsi 炳靈寺石窟 (Luminous Spirits Temple) near Lanzhou 
* Maijishan 麥積山石窟
* Lashaosi 拉稍寺石窟 on 武山
* Jintasi 金塔寺
* Matisi 马蹄寺石窟 (Horse Hoof Temple)
* 北石窟寺, 南石窟寺 Longdongshiku

NINGXIA 
* Xumishan 須彌山石窟 northwest of Guyuan 固原

XINJIANG
* Tuyugou 吐峪溝石窟 (Toyuq)
* Keqier 克孜尔千佛洞 ([[Kizil]] or Qizil; jap.: キジル石窟)

HEBEI
* Xiangtanshan 响堂山石窟 [[@http://xts.uchicago.edu/|online reconstruction project]] 

HENAN
* Longmen [[龍門石窟]] near Luoyang 洛陽
* Gongxian [[巩县石窟]] near Zhengzhou 鄭州


===Official State Monasteries in the Tang===
* 大雲　monasteries founded or named by 武則天
* 開元　monasteries founded or named by 唐玄宗
* [[西明寺]] in 長安 established by 唐高宗　in 656, [[玄奘]] translated the sutras here which he brought back from India, also [[義淨]], [[空海]] studied Sanskrit here 

> ====Literature====
* D.C. Twitchett: The Monasteries and China's Economy in Medieval Times. Bulletin of the School of Oriental and African Studies, University of London , Vol. 19, No. 3 (1957): 526-549 [[@http://www.jstor.org/stable/609825|JSTOR]]
* D.C. Twitchett:　Monastic Estates in T'ang China. Asia Major, Vol. 5, No. 2 (1956): 123-146 [[http://www.ihp.sinica.edu.tw/~asiamajor/pdf/1956/1956-123.pdf|pdf]] 

